### 🟡 Cảnh báo Logic/Tối ưu — Reviewed & Resolved

| # | Item | Resolution |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | `OnValidate` inheritance chain — must use `protected virtual` / `protected override` with `base.OnValidate()` calls | ✅ Correctly implemented. `BaseUnitData` declares `protected virtual`, all children use `protected override` with `base.OnValidate()`. |
| 2 | `#if UNITY_EDITOR` around virtual methods — could cause build issues if method signature is stripped | ✅ Safe — both `virtual` declaration and all `override` declarations are consistently wrapped in `#if UNITY_EDITOR`, so the entire chain is stripped uniformly in builds. |
| 3 | `faction` field still exposed in Inspector on child types — designer could change it | ✅ Mitigated — `DefenderUnitData.OnValidate()` auto-corrects to `Ally`, `EnemyUnitData.OnValidate()` auto-corrects to `Enemy`, with a warning log. |
| 4 | `HeroCardData.linkedUnitData` typed as `BaseUnitData` — could accept `EnemyUnitData` | ✅ Existing `OnValidate` on line 206 checks `linkedUnitData.faction != UnitFaction.Ally` and warns. No code change needed. |
| 5 | `EnemySpawnEntry.enemyData` faction check removed in `LevelConfig.OnValidate` | ✅ Correct — `EnemyUnitData` enforces `faction = Enemy` in its own `OnValidate`, so the LevelConfig check was redundant. Type system now prevents wrong assignment. |
| 6 | `GetType().Name` used in `BaseUnitData` and `DefenderUnitData` log messages | ✅ Good pattern — prints the actual concrete class name (e.g., "CombatDefenderData") instead of the parent class name, improving debug readability. |

